.TH IMGMOD 1 "July 7, 2026" "imgmod 1.0.0"
.SH NAME
imgmod \- Image modification helpers
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B imgmod
[\fB-h\fR|\fB--help\fR]
.br
.B imgmod
[\fB-v\fR|\fB--version\fR]
.br
.B imgmod
[\fB-o\fR] \fICOMMAND\fR [\fIOPTIONS\fR] [\fIARGS\fR]
.br
.B imgmod
\fB-n\fR \fINAME-OR-PATH\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B imgmod
is a plugin-based wrapper for image modification commands.

Commands are executable plugin files named \fBimgmod-\fICOMMAND\fR. Users run
plugins through the wrapper as \fBimgmod \fICOMMAND\fR.

Bundled plugins are installed next to the wrapper. Local plugins are searched
from XDG data directories before bundled plugins, so local plugins can override
bundled commands.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B completion
Print shell completion data and generated completion scripts.
.TP
.B newplugin
Create a new imgmod plugin from a template.
.TP
.B socshare
Crop and resize an image to 1200x630 for social sharing.
.TP
.B help \fICOMMAND\fR
Show help for a command.
.TP
.B version
Show script name and version number.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-h, --help
Show usage help.
.TP
.B \-n \fINAME-OR-PATH\fR
Create a new plugin. This is a shortcut for \fBimgmod newplugin\fR.
.TP
.B \-o
Optimize plugin image outputs with \fBimage_optim\fR.
Only files reported by a plugin with \fBimgmod_output\fR are optimized.
.TP
.B \-v, --version
Show script name and version number.
.SH PLUGIN LOOKUP
Plugin lookup order is:
.TP
1.
\fB$XDG_DATA_HOME/imgmod/plugins\fR, defaulting to
\fB$HOME/.local/share/imgmod/plugins\fR.
.TP
2.
Each \fB$XDG_DATA_DIRS\fR entry with \fB/imgmod/plugins\fR appended,
defaulting to \fB/usr/local/share/imgmod/plugins\fR and
\fB/usr/share/imgmod/plugins\fR.
.TP
3.
Bundled plugins next to the \fBimgmod\fR wrapper.
.SH PLUGIN API
Plugins that use \fBlib/imgmod.sh\fR define hooks named from their command
prefix, such as \fBwatermark_start\fR, and call
\fBimgmod_plugin_run "$@"\fR.

Plugins call \fBimgmod_output \fIFILE\fR to report image output files that can
be optimized with \fBimgmod -o\fR.
.SH FILES
.TP
.B ~/.local/share/imgmod/plugins/imgmod-*
User plugin executables.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Create a social sharing image:
.nf
.B imgmod socshare image.png
.fi
.TP
Create and optimize a social sharing image:
.nf
.B imgmod -o socshare image.png
.fi
.TP
Create a new local plugin:
.nf
.B imgmod newplugin watermark
.fi
.TP
List completion command candidates:
.nf
.B imgmod completion commands
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR imgmod-completion (1),
.BR imgmod-newplugin (1),
.BR imgmod-socshare (1)
